[35:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'They were certainly nowhere near the solution of their problem. "The poor little things," cried Cynthia, "think of them having been turned to the wall all these years. Now, what is the sense of it?" And the performance is'

[36:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'quite impressive. I mean, if you compare this with other multimodal models of similar sizes, note that this new UniMo, on average, performs the best. By the way, if you\'re interested in the'

[36:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'architecture of this, it consists of a few key components. First of all, it has a unified encoding layer, which can take in and encode audio, images, or video, or text into tokens. This then gets plugged through this omnimodality 3D'

[36:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'rope layer, so that it can keep track of where and when things happen. So, it doesn\'t matter if it\'s audio or a video or text, it can keep track of the contact of all these inputs via this self-attention layer with 3D rope. And'

[36:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then, it also has this dynamic router to efficiently determine where to route the data through this team of experts. So, think of this as like a team of AI agents working together to, you know, solve your task. But, with this dynamic'

[37:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'router, it makes it more efficient. It\'s able to determine which agent is best for solving which task. And then, afterwards, it would go through this decoder component to output either text or audio or images. The awesome thing'

[37:13] [scene:talk]
